Eden Moringa Production and Marketers  yesterday announced plans to train Nigerian Moringa farmers on basic necessity required in farming for maximum profitability. The training which will commence April 14 2022, is centred on the topic, “Harnessing Economic Potentials, Entrepreneurship on Opportunity and Health Benefit” and seek to empower youths and women on practical solutions to the rejection of Nigerian agricultural products by foreign countries and to build character that enhance profitable farming cultivation among others. Addressing newsmen yesterday in Abuja, president of Eden Moringa Production and Marketers Limited, Dr Michael Ashimashiga said the objective of the training was to equip farmers with requisite skills on obtaining production, drying and packaging knowledge of organic food products for export, healthy life and other benefits. He said, “While we strive for the understanding of the federal government of Nigeria and all its agencies in giving maximum support to Eden Moringa and Eden Group Farmers for the changing of our present situations for the good of all citizens through Moringa productions and export, we shall also continue to seek for the support of all our registered farmers and investors to keep praying for Eden as put our footprint in all the countries of the world for a better reward for all of us”.